    {
      "id": "30a9964500054e131c27be7281101fde91a1ca0c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-06-25 19:30:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(12 inline comments)\n\nActually iobuf_pool has been moved to osd_layer, added into osd_thread_info in new ofd/osd changes. so in 2.4. we will not need filter_iobuf at all, if we plan to throw away obdfilter at that time. Is this change necessary for 2.3? seems so according to your comments?\n\nNo serious problem in the patch, but I would prefer you to fix them before landing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "a79c5b35af67de51040135bb799acc98c0d3e4f4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-06-26 02:07:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: (12 inline comments)\n\nthanks for review, please check inline replies.\n\nAbout iobuf_pool, I know it's under changing, however, if I don't make this change right now, my patch might crash OSS, as I said we don't have absolute threads limit anymore, which means we can't pre-allocate a \"big enough\" array to store iobuf_pool, that's the reason I add cfs_hash for this to avoid pre-allocating a huge array.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
